5 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Why do people do what they do?</span><hr size=1> I wanted to relate to you something that happened to a real life friend of mine while he was trying to have fun playing EQ.<br>
<br>
My friend was doing some trading with Canelron(spelling?), trying to trade a mistmoore drum for 400 plat.  Nothing really remarkable about that right? Well, instead of the mismoore drum, he accidentaly traded away his Walrus Skin drum!!  the walrus skin drum is worth far more than a mistmoore drum, and much more than 400 plat.  Here is the kick in the nuts though; canelron refused to give it back!  <br>
<br>
why? Why do people do theses kinds of things?  do they not know that this is NOT the way to make friends? I suppose it doesn't really matter to them that they ruined someones day.<br>
It may matter later on when they find out they have made a bad reputation for themselves! Will the theft of a Walrus skin drum make up for that?<br>
<br>
thanks for listening to my rant.  im sure we all have similar stories to tell, and id like to hear them.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/ukestramysticheart.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kestra Mysticheart</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Power Poster</span><br>  Posts: 91<br> <font color=#330000>(11/15/01 6:57:29 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why do people do what they do?</span><hr size=1> I have heard many debates about people not believing they had to act ethically in a game. Doesn't reflect on their real life person.. yada yada yada... Only answer really is greed. <br>
<br>
Anyway, I have a walrus skin drum rotting in the bank. If it was your friends best percussion instrument you are welcome to grab it for him.<br>
<br>
