 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/ucrowleywayfinder.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Crowley Wayfinder</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 326<br> <font color=#330000>(11/16/01 11:10:37 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.lcdmultimedia.com/crowley.jpg W=104 H=200></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why do people do what they do?</span><hr size=1> The answer to this one is pretty simple. <br>
<br>
How many people did you know growing up that cheated when playing games? <br>
<br>
I am sure you can think of a few. Some people cheated the dice, some people marked the cards, other people brow beat the Dungeon Master into making the Saving Throw.<br>
<br>
Now... <br>
<br>
Take all those people, give them a cheap interactive online game... and allow ALL of them to become COMPLETELY ANONYMOUS. They cannot be tracked down. They cannot be held accountable. There are NO moral/social repercussions for their actions.<br>
<br>
Welcome to EverQuest... &quot;You're in our World Now&quot;<br>
<br>
P.S. Its good to know that some people are capable of policing themselves. You are a class act Gaggrog. We will get you those beads. <p>--------------------------<BR>
